# GAIPS CI Pipeline — Python dependency source (CORE group)
#
# Scope: this lists the packages THIS (static) .gitlab-ci.yml pipeline installs.
# The AI red-team / live-eval tools (garak, giskard, inspect-ai, inspect-evals,
# pyrit) belong to the SEPARATE live-scans pipeline and are intentionally NOT here.
#
# The pipeline's deps don't reliably co-resolve as one lockfile: the markllm
# watermark stack pins old huggingface_hub<1.0 / Pillow==9.4.0, and the data
# quality group (evidently + ydata-profiling) pins narrow numpy/pandas ranges.
# Those packages also run in ISOLATED per-job venvs, so they never actually share
# one environment.
#
# Therefore the source list is split into independently-resolvable GROUPS, one
# file each, all matching the glob `requirements-ci*.in`:
#
#   requirements-ci.in              <- this file (core foundational tools)
#   requirements-ci-markllm.in      <- markllm watermark stack (also markllm-deps-audit)
#   requirements-ci-dataquality.in  <- great-expectations / evidently / ydata / dvc
#
# The `lockfile-audit` job compiles + pip-audits EACH group on its own and merges
# the per-group results into one lockfile-audit.json. A group that still cannot be
# resolved into a single lockfile is reported as a WARNING (not a failure) -- its
# packages remain covered at runtime by the per-job `.audit-env` after_script.
#
# Regenerate a group lock locally on a Python 3.11-slim Linux container:
#   pip install pip-tools
#   pip-compile --generate-hashes --output-file requirements-ci.txt requirements-ci.in
#
# This CORE group is the candidate for the committed, hash-pinned requirements-ci.txt
# (Fix #0 "teeth": pin CI installs to it with --require-hashes once it is green).

# -- Vault / secrets ----------------------------------------------------------
hvac

# -- Package auditing ---------------------------------------------------------
pip-audit
pip-tools

# -- Model signing / integrity ------------------------------------------------
model-signing
sigstore

# -- Model scanning -----------------------------------------------------------
modelscan
huggingface_hub

# -- HTTP / data (shared) -----------------------------------------------------
requests
pandas

# -- Eval-dataset contract validation (eval-dataset-validate) -----------------
jsonschema

# -- Data redaction -- PII (dataset-redact); secrets handled by gitleaks binary
presidio-analyzer
presidio-anonymizer
# NOTE: dataset-redact also runs `python -m spacy download en_core_web_sm`
# (spaCy is pulled in transitively by presidio-analyzer).

# -- Evidence reporting -------------------------------------------------------
jinja2
